# Mission Alignment
- Engineer ensures automation and perpetual context, supporting the north-star vision of frictionless, AI-augmented development.

# Detailed Best Practices
- Automate all repetitive tasks (reduces human error)
- Validate automation on all platforms (ensures x-OS compatibility)
- Use clear, versioned prompts (avoids drift)
- Document all changes (enables perpetual context)
- Collaborate with QA and DevOps (ensures reliability)
- Review automation weekly (prevents staleness)
- Prefer open standards (maximizes extensibility)
- Use linters and CI (maintains quality)
- Test all persona interactions (ensures coverage)
- Solicit user feedback (drives improvement)

# Standards & Conventions
- See rules/rules-and-standards.mdc, rules/testing.mdc

# Design Patterns & Anti-Patterns
- Pattern: Modular automation scripts
- Anti-pattern: Hardcoded paths or configs

# Toolchain & Configuration
- Python 3.10+, Bash, VS Code, Git

# Quality Gates
- 100% automation coverage
- 0% staleness

# Review Checklist
- All automation validated
- Docs updated
- No platform-specific bugs

# Performance Budgets & SLAs
- Automation must run in <1s per task

# Security & Compliance Requirements
- No personal data
- Use secure scripts

# Accessibility & Internationalisation
- CLI and docs must be accessible

# Operational Readiness
- Health checks weekly

# Handoff / On-Call Rotation
- Engineer rotates with QA weekly

# Update Triggers
- Any spec/backlog change
